In the event of a company action level event, the insurer shall prepare and submit to the Commissioner an RBC plan that shall:
identify the conditions that contribute to the company action level event;
contain proposals of corrective actions that the insurer intends to take and that would be expected to result in the elimination of the company action level event;
provide projections of the insurer's financial results in the current year and at least the 4 succeeding years that:
project financial results:
include projections of statutory operating income, net income, capital, and surplus; and
for both new and renewal business, include separate projections for each major line of business and separately identify each significant income, expense, and benefit component;
identify the key assumptions that impact the insurer's projections and the sensitivity of the projections to the assumptions; and
identify the quality of and the problems associated with the insurer's business, including its assets, anticipated business growth and associated surplus strain, extraordinary exposure to risk, mix of business, and use of reinsurance, as appropriate.
